step_data.thought:
I've successfully switched to the ÖPNVKarte layer, which is focused on public transportation networks. This is evident from the images loaded from the tileserver.memomaps.de server (elements [579] through [596]). 

So far, I've explored three different map layers for New York City:
1. Standard (the default layer)
2. CyclOSM (focused on cycling routes and infrastructure)
3. ÖPNVKarte (focused on public transportation)

There's one more layer left to explore according to the layer menu: Humanitarian. Let's switch to this final layer to complete my exploration of the different map layers available for New York City in OpenStreetMap.
